Solution: 
First, we need to evaluate $(3.6)^2$.
\begin{align*}
(3.6)^2 &= 12.96
\end{align*}
Next, we need to evaluate $\lceil 3.6 \rceil$.
\begin{align*}
\lceil 3.6 \rceil &= 4
\end{align*}
Then, we need to evaluate $\lceil 12.96 \rceil$.
\begin{align*}
\lceil 12.96 \rceil &= 13
\end{align*}
Finally, we need to evaluate $\lceil (3.6)^2 \rceil - ( \lceil 3.6 \rceil ) ^2$.
\begin{align*}
\lceil (3.6)^2 \rceil - ( \lceil 3.6 \rceil ) ^2 &= 13 - 4^2 \\
&= 13 - 16 \\
&= -3
\end{align*}
Therefore, the answer is $\boxed{-3}$.

